**Criando um bucket de armazenamento de objetos com CLI**

1. Execute o comando `oci object storage bucket create --name <nome_do_bucket>` (por exemplo, `oci object storage bucket create --name my-bucket`).
2. Configure a política de armazenamento de objetos: `oci object storage bucket policy set --bucket <nome_do_bucket> --policy <política>` (por exemplo, `oci object storage bucket policy set --bucket my-bucket --policy { "Version": 1, "Statement": [ { "Sid": "AllowObjectStorage", "Effect": "Allow", "Principal": { "Service": "object_storage" }, "Action": "object_storage:PutObject" } ] }`).

**Implementando pre-authenticated requests com CLI**

1. Execute o comando `oci object storage key create --key <nome_do_key>` (por exemplo, `oci object storage key create --key my-key`).
2. Configure a política de pre-authenticated requests: `oci object storage bucket policy add --bucket <nome_do_bucket> --key <nome_do_key> --policy <política>` (por exemplo, `oci object storage bucket policy add --bucket my-bucket --key my-key --policy { "Version": 1, "Statement": [ { "Sid": "AllowPreAuthenticatedRequests", "Effect": "Allow", "Principal": { "Service": "object_storage" }, "Action": "object_storage:PutObject" } ] }`).

**Implementando lifecycle policies com CLI**

1. Execute o comando `oci object storage lifecycle policy create --name <nome_da_política>` (por exemplo, `oci object storage lifecycle policy create --name my-lifecycle-policy`).
2. Configure a política de armazenamento de objetos com a política de vida: `oci object storage lifecycle policy add --policy <nome_da_política> --rule <regra>` (por exemplo, `oci object storage lifecycle policy add --policy my-lifecycle-policy --rule { "Name": "DeleteAfter1Day", "Action": "Delete" }`).

**Implementando versioning com CLI**

1. Execute o comando `oci object storage bucket versioning enable --bucket <nome_do_bucket>` (por exemplo, `oci object storage bucket versioning enable --bucket my-bucket`).

